sense.name: make or be full of cavities
sense.examples: Our puddles of light showed walls honeycombed with small square niches. His old writing desk was a walnut monster honeycombed with secret compartments. The hills they entered were honeycombed. Memorial Reef is a waist-high, honeycombed igloo. The terrain is honeycombed with the hidden trails. Land sheered upward, buckling into mountains honeycombed by caves.

sense.name: infiltrate thoroughly
sense.examples: That law enforcement organization is honeycombed with corruption and incompetence My whole double-damned staff must be honeycombed with his snoops. The revolutionaries honeycombed the organization It is a text honeycombed with myriad verbal links. He must have Dan's offices honeycombed with snoops.
